                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d356">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/3783: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-09-07T18:00:00-06:00"
                            >September 7, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>180. Minister for Foreign Affairs told me this morning that he was telegraphing
                    Mexican representatives in important South American countries to endeavor to
                    secure cooperation of respective countries in bringing influence to bear on
                    present Cuban Government to maintain order and to protect foreign interests in
                    Cuba. Foreign Office has just telephoned that telegrams have been sent to
                    Argentina, Brazil and Chile and that Mexican Chargé d’Affaires had been fully
                    informed of Mexican position.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Daniels</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
